### app/error.tsx

In App Router, `error.tsx` must be a client component. It receives `error` and `reset` props.

```tsx
'use client';

export default function Error({
  error,
  reset,
}: {
  error: Error & { digest?: string };
  reset: () => void;
}) {
  return (
    <div className="error-page">
      <h1>Something went wrong!</h1>
      <p>{error.message || 'An unexpected error occurred.'}</p>
      <button onClick={() => reset()}>Try again</button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

The old `_error.js` used `getInitialProps` to get the status code. In App Router, the `error.tsx` is simpler — it's an error boundary. For custom error handling per status code, we'd use `not-found.tsx` for 404 and `error.tsx` for other errors.

